<h3>Description</h3>
<p>A data type for storing an 8-bit number, values of 0 to 255.</p>


<h3>Example</h3>

<code>
    var
        time : byte;
        lives ; byte = 3;
        zeroVal : byte at $01; // declared at memory location 1.
        p : ^byte; // Pointer to a byte. same as "pointer of byte".

    begin
        lives := lives - 1;
</code>
